A static import blocks execution in its context and waits until the import is loaded and excuted, which is asynchronous, but from the point of view of the context, synchronous, as execution in context is blocked.

A dynamic import returns a promise, so one can await for it.

Exporting a promise for a import, just returns that promise from the import.
Lets assume a promise is exported, then:
```javascript
//static import
import bla from 'promise_export';
// bla will be the exportet promise
result = await bla;

// dynamic import
bla = await import('bla');
// bla will be the exportet promise
result = await bla;
```

