We can go 2 ways now, either we make string/encoding.rb mandatory, which I see it already kind of is, or we write some "polyfill" functions. At first I implemented those functions, but decide to not include them in a patch.

```ruby
  # If corelib/string/encoding isn't loaded, below are the methods that
